verbose_text: We find that the transcriptional level of GFAT1 is much more up-regulated in HepG2.2.15 as compared with HepG2 (XREF_FIG), and, correspondingly, the levels of UDP-N-acetyl glucosamine (UDP-GlcNAc) and UDP-N-acetyl galactosamine (UDP-GalNAc), the most abundant end products of HBP, are markedly increased in HepG2.2.15 cells (XREF_FIG).
